An avid Republican, he attended several national conventions as a delegate, and in 1924 he refused the party's nomination for governor of Texas. He twice married, the first to Second Person on July 14, 1892. Before she died on June 21, 1895, however, the union produced one child,
column5: Third Person, who later became the wife of Talbot Frederick Rothwell.

column4: She referred to her experience at GFC as ``The Graduate School in Sensory Evaluation''. During this time she discerned, under the mentoring of First Person, the importance of correlation among objective sensory, instrumental, product, and consumer opinion data collection. In the early 1970s, while raising her children,
column5: Civille decided to move into the world of sensory analysis as an independent consultant, expanding the sensory world by applying her experience gained at GFC for the benefit of consumers.

column4: She has the distinction of being the first female and person of African-American descent to win the title. column4: In a draft of his unpublished autobiography, First Person wrote that Second Person refused to name the model, but told him it was the wife of a lawyer who lived above his Manhattan apartment (First Person, in a later version, omitted the location, saying only that Second Person said it was the wife of a lawyer friend). column5: Fourth Person's daughter, noted in her edition of her father's letters that Elsie had been the model for Second Person's dime and half dollar.

Also in 1974, Second Person teamed up with

column4: She was delivered to the Norwegian passenger ship company Det Bergenske Dampskibsselskab of Bergen in 1905. Irma sailed for the company until she was attacked and sunk by two MTBs belonging to the Royal Norwegian Navy on 13 February 1944. After delivery, Irma served on the
column5: Bergen-- Newcastle route until she was transferred to Norway in the autumn of 1921 to carry out tourist voyages to the North Cape and Spitsbergen in the summer seasons.

column4: Meg and First Person each have three siblings, and have a closer relationship with their youngest brother than with other family members. Like Second Person, First Person learns to silently communicate with a male love interest via kything. Third Person is about two years older than
column5: Fourth Person, her contemporary.
